Issues.Body:
In a vuex action I have a simple block of code in which I am simply calling Vue.router.push() in a method of vuex

Relevant code:

```
import Vue from 'vue'

login ({ commit }, data) {
  Vue.router.push({
    name: 'dashboard'
  }, () => {
    store.dispatch('app/loaded')
  })
}

```
What is expected:
The onComplete callback of the router.push call should be executed.

What is actually happening:
The onComplete callback never gets executed after upgrading to 3.0.5 from 3.0.4

Additional info:
I rolled back to 3.0.4 and this issue went away. This is code that I have not touched in 6 months and has had many vue-router upgrades without issue.

